      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Even a single dose of ibuprofen at 200mg or 400mg can pose a risk to your kidneys, especially if you have chronic kidney disease (CKD). While the short-term effects may not be immediately apparent, ibuprofen can lead to kidney injury over time, particularly if used frequently. It's essential to consider the cumulative impact on your kidneys, and discuss your options with your healthcare provider to avoid potential risks.",
      "source": "target",
